DistroForge Debian packaging
=============================

This package uses dh-sequence-python3 with pybuild-plugin-pyproject.

The imported 0.3.5-1 Git baseline carries the Ubuntu resolute
Standards-Version adjustment directly in the source. No Quilt patches are
active in this baseline.

Standalone development remains driven by pyproject.toml and a local virtual
environment. Debian package builds should use distribution Python packages from
debian/control instead of pip-installed dependencies.

During alpha development, local binary package builds are intentionally outside
the default workflow. Use lint, tests, import checks and static packaging review
unless the maintainer explicitly asks for a package build in the current task.

For a source upload, create an upstream orig tarball that excludes local build
artifacts such as .venv, __pycache__, .pytest_cache, .ruff_cache and egg-info.

If build dependency inspection is needed, review the dependencies listed in
debian/control without producing package artifacts.
